{"description":"Tiny ajax","updated_at":"2012-01-17T08:54:03Z","git_push_url":"git@gist.github.com:1625623.git","comments":7,"files":{"test.html":{"type":"text/html","filename":"test.html","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1625623/e66aec859186768165ab43c90318996e939891e9/test.html","language":"HTML","size":388,"content":"<!DOCTYPE html> \n<title>Tiny xhr</title>\n<div>Expected value: <b>pass</b></div>\n<div>Actual value: <b id=\"ret\">loading...</b></div>\n<script>\n  var tiny_ajax = function(m,u,c,d){with(new XMLHttpRequest)onreadystatechange=function(){readyState^4||c(this)},open(m,u),send(d)};\n\n  tiny_ajax('get', '.', function (xhr){\n     document.getElementById( \"ret\" ).innerHTML = \"pass\";\n  });\n</script>"},"README.md":{"type":"text/plain","filename":"README.md","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1625623/cb875927c0654a43f00751d86faf68acd48aab16/README.md","language":"Markdown","size":699,"content":"Tiny ajax: xhr get, post, whatever - for modern browsers in 130 bytes\n=========\n\n```javascript\nfunction tiny_ajax(method, url, callback, post_data) {/* ... */}\n\n// asynch call\ntiny_ajax('get', '.', function (xhr) {\n    console.log(xhr.responseText);\n});\n\ntiny_ajax('post', '.', function (xhr) {\n    console.log(xhr.responseText);\n}, 'data');\n\n// synch call\nvar xhr = tiny_ajax('get', '.');\n\nvar xhr = tiny_ajax('post', '.', 0, 'data');\n```\n\nDemo: http://jsfiddle.net/y3msq/\n\nThere is also crossbrowse one, but 155 bytes long\n\n```javascript\nfunction(m,u,c,d){with(new(this.XMLHttpRequest||ActiveXObject)(\"Microsoft.XMLHTTP\"))onreadystatechange=function(){readyState^4||c(this)},open(m,u),send(d)}\n```"},"LICENSE.txt":{"type":"text/plain","filename":"LICENSE.txt","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1625623/24d1c06476ea3c40766cde9ce44d29253636a7fd/LICENSE.txt","language":"Text","size":495,"content":"            DO WHAT THE FUCK YOU WANT TO PUBLIC LICENSE\n                    Version 2, December 2004\n\n Copyright (C) 2011 Mikhail Davydov <azazel.private@gmail.com>\n\n Everyone is permitted to copy and distribute verbatim or modified\n copies of this license document, and changing it is allowed as long\n as the name is changed.\n\n            DO WHAT THE FUCK YOU WANT TO PUBLIC LICENSE\n   TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR COPYING, DISTRIBUTION AND MODIFICATION\n\n  0. You just DO WHAT THE FUCK YOU WANT TO."},"annotated.js":{"type":"application/javascript","filename":"annotated.js","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1625623/21a32bbe6293bd54022cd07d954024d88e8b6fbc/annotated.js","language":"JavaScript","size":482,"content":"function(\n  m, // method - get, post, whatever\n  u, // url\n  c, // [callback] if passed -> asych call\n  d, // [post_data]\n  x\n){\n    with(x=new XMLHttpRequest)\n        return onreadystatechange=function(){ // filter only readyState=4 events\n            readyState^4||c(this) // if callback passed and readyState == 4 than trigger Callback with xhr object\n        },\n        open(m,u,c), // open connection with Method and Url and asyCh flag\n        send(d), // send Data\n        x\n}"},"package.json":{"type":"application/json","filename":"package.json","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1625623/852a0fa3dc2bb846945d1b140cf69a21bb33aa88/package.json","language":"JSON","size":183,"content":"{\n  \"name\": \"tiny_ajax\",\n\n  \"description\": \"Tiny ajax: xhr get, post, whatever... for modern browsers\",\n\n  \"keywords\": [\n    \"xhr\",\n    \"get\",\n    \"post\",\n    \"tiny\",\n    \"ajax\"\n  ]\n}"},"index.js":{"type":"application/javascript","filename":"index.js","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1625623/8f6055c7af4f257b6b1428af61f8f2874a553aad/index.js","language":"JavaScript","size":128,"content":"function(m,u,c,d,x){with(x=new XMLHttpRequest)return onreadystatechange=function(){readyState^4||c(this)},open(m,u,c),send(d),x}"}},"fork_of":{"description":"140byt.es -- Click ↑↑ fork ↑↑ to play!","updated_at":"2011-05-18T12:15:41Z","git_push_url":"git@gist.github